        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued May 8 at 5:59PM EDT until May 8 at 6:15PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 559 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 10 miles southwest
of Shelby, or near Boiling Springs NC, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Two inch hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect wind
damage to trees and power lines.

Locations impacted include...
Cliffside, Mooresboro, Henrietta, Boiling Springs NC, Ellenboro,
Lattimore, Caroleen, Patterson Springs, and Shelby.
</description>
        <instruction>This storm is producing large hail. SEEK SHELTER NOW inside a sturdy
structure and stay away from windows.</instruction>
